name: Eccentric Heel Drop
description: Focuses on lengthening the calf muscles to improve strength and mobility.

name: Heel Raise
description: Targets the calves by raising the heels to build strength and endurance.

name: Seated Calf Raise
description: Isolates the calves, particularly the soleus muscle, in a seated position.

name: Standing Calf Raise
description: Strengthens the calf muscles by raising the heels from a standing position.

name: Standing Calf Raise (Machine)
description: Targets the calves with added resistance from the machine for increased intensity.

name: Standing Calf Raise (Dumbbell)
description: Engages the calves using dumbbells to add resistance to the standing raise.

name: Standing Calf Raise (Smith Machine)
description: Stabilized calf raise using the Smith machine for controlled resistance.

name: Standing Calf Raise (Barbell)
description: Utilizes a barbell for added weight in a standing calf raise, enhancing muscle growth.

name: Calf Extension (Machine)
description: Uses a machine to extend the calves and build strength through resistance.

name: Calf Press (Machine)
description: Engages the calves using a machine for press movement to develop power.

name: Single Standing Calf Raise (Machine)
description: Isolates each calf with a single-leg movement for balanced strength development.

name: Donkey Calf Raise
description: Targets the calves by bending at the waist and raising the heels, often performed with added weight.

name: Single-Leg Calf Raise
description: Isolates each calf muscle individually by performing calf raises on one leg.

name: Single-Leg Calf Raise (Dumbbell)
description: Adds resistance to the single-leg calf raise by holding a dumbbell.

name: Jump Rope
description: A cardio exercise that strengthens the calves through repetitive jumping motions.

name: Farmer's Walk on Toes
description: Enhances calf strength and stability by walking on toes while carrying weights.

name: Calf Raise with Resistance Band
description: Targets the calves by adding resistance from a band during heel raises.

name: Plié Squat Calf Raise
description: Combines a plié squat with a calf raise to engage the calves and lower body.

name: Box Jump
description: Plyometric exercise that strengthens the calves and lower body through explosive jumps onto a box.
